// so toh as according to EF-codd(computerscientist also called father of dbms), for a Table to be in a SecondNormalForm there is 2-requirements:-
//  1st. that table should be in FirstNormalForm
//  2nd. that table should not contain partial-dependencies, mtlb ki table meh jo non-prime-Attributes(or mtlb non-CandidateKeys aur ya mtlb ki voh keys joki candidate-Key k bnnne meh participate nhi hoti) hai voh sabhi should be fully functional-dependent on Candidate-Key, mtlb partially koi bhi dependent nhi hona chahiyehh. thus toh mtlb enn non-primeAttributes ko fully functional-dependent hona hai on the "Candidate-key". whereas yaha "fully" functional-dependent hone ka mtlb hai ki esa koi case ya situation nhi honi chahiyehh jismeh yeh Attribute(non-prime-Attribute) ki value "Candidate-key" se find/determine nhi ho pr rhi ho, toh mtlb "nhi ho pa ri ho" wali baat nhi honi chahiyehh in SecondNormalForm.

// now here "partial-dependencies" ka mtlb ki:-
// toh jaise in pic2, apn dekh rhe hai ki non-prime-Attribute(mtlb here it is location-attribute) is just only dependent of storeId mtlb it is partially-dependent on candidate-keY(where candidateKey is a composite of storeId and CustomerId), so toh mtlb yeh aseh Candidate-key pe "partial-Dependency" nhi honi chaiyehh, mtlb Candidate-key pe fully dependency honi chahiyehh.
// so the solution of "partial-dependency" is ki divide or break or decompose the table into sub-tables and connect them by introducing "foreign-key".
// thus toh "partial-dependency" ka yeh mtlb hai ki agr kisi table meh there are more than one "candidate-keys" then jo non-candidatekeys(or non-candidateAttributes or mtlb non-primeKeys) hai voh uss composite-CandidateKey se functional-dependent hone chahiyehh , mtlb esa nhi ki voh non-primeAttributes Composite-CandidateKey k kuchi attributes pe "dependent" hai, jaise ki apnne pic2.example meh dekha tha ki "location"-attribute composite-Candidate-Key k sirf "storeId-attribue" pe hi dependent tha, and agr apn useeh dono storeId and customerId se dependent krna cha rhe the tab vaha inconsistency/problem aa rhi thi ki uske according apnko yeh lg rha that ki location-delhi ek nhi alg-alg hai, but voh toh actually meh ek hi hai.

// and ya "partial-dependency" ko aseh bhi bol sktehh hai ki koi bhi non-prime-Attribute is can be independently determined by a part-of-CandidateKey then mtlb there is a "partial-dependency".